        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>Text and illustrations prepared in cooperation with FABCO Automotive Corporation.</para>
                <para>Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0201001">Figure 1</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <para>The drive axle consists of four major assemblies:</para>
                <figure id="f0201001" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg02/G0201001.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Cross Section of Drive End</caption>
                </figure>
                <seqlist>
                    <item>
                        <para>Axle housing, which is the backbone of the assembly.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Differential carrier, which bolts into the center of the axle housing.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Tie rod assembly, which is linkage connecting the left and right steerable drive ends.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Steering arms, which connect steering drive ends to vehicle's steering system and the
                            steering drive ends together with the tie rod.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                </seqlist>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
